Florida International University is a two year upper division University in the State University System of Florida.
 The Mathematical Sciences Department is located within the College of Arts and Sciences, and offers three undergraduate major programs: mathematics, computer science, and statistics.
 The computing facilities available are quite good. The computer center operates a UNIVAC 1106 with an adequate array of peripherals, terminals, and memory. In addition, the department owns a NOVA 2/10 mini-computer and an IMLAC PDS-4 intelligent graphics system.